Feature 1 — recording limit 10min → 300min
============================================

Four edits. Three smali (runtime behavior + UI formatter fix) + one layout
XML (UI label). Java reference: src/feature1_recording_limit/AudioRecorder.patch.java

---------------------------------------------------------------
File: smali_classes2/com/wisky/libnotewritercomponent/audio/AudioUtil$Companion.smali

Removes a "freeze seconds at 10min" dead branch that becomes visible once the
cap is lifted. Original Java (formatMillis):

    if (minutes == 10) {
        return String.format("%02d:%02d", minutes, 0);   // "10:00" for 60s
    }

At :cond_0, drop the three comparison instructions and jump straight to the
normal mm:ss path:

  -    :cond_0
  -    const-wide/16 v0, 0xa
  -    cmp-long p2, v2, v0
  -    const/4 v0, 0x2
  -    .line 60
  -    const-string v1, "%02d:%02d"
  -    if-nez p2, :cond_1
  +    :cond_0
  +    const/4 v0, 0x2
  +    .line 60
  +    const-string v1, "%02d:%02d"
  +    goto :cond_1

The MM:00 branch body that used to fall through is now unreachable dead code
(apktool assembles it fine).


